summaries.short: With Joxe Mari on the run and threats against Txato escalating, life becomes difficult for both Bittori's and Miren's families.
summaries.full: With Joxe Mari the subject of a massive police hunt, Miren turns to the only person she can trust--Bittori--but unintentionally divulges Txato's secret in the process. Meanwhile, as Nerea and her friends are confronted by the police, Txato and Bittori navigate the fallout of escalating threats from ETA.

summaries.short: Bittori writes a letter to Joxe Mari asking him to speak about what happened on the day of the attack.
summaries.full: Bittori writes a letter to Joxe Mari asking him to speak about what happened on the day of the attack.

summaries.short: While Bittori breaks the estrangement between families by asking Joxian for a favor, their children reunite and bond over Txato's kindness.
summaries.full: Bittori is visited by her son Xabier and daughter Nerea, who come bearing surprising news. Meanwhile, though their parents no longer speak, an encounter at the hospital reunites Xabier with Miren and Joxian's daughter Arantxa, providing him an opportunity to return something special from their childhood--and further piquing Miren's suspicions as a result.

summaries.short: ETA issues a dangerous set of orders for Joxe Mari and increases their pressure on Txato.
summaries.full: While local resentment towards Txato reaches a fever pitch, Joxe Mari's shadowy ETA superiors enlist him to execute a series of hits. Later, news of Txato's murder breaks, and a devasted Bittori's grief deepens as she's warned against having his funeral in town, while Joxian grapples with the death of his friend from a distance.

summaries.short: Arantxa's budding friendship with Bittori drives her to go behind her mother's back and reach out to Joxe Mari with an urgent request.
summaries.full: Realizing she has more in common with Joxe Mari than she thought, Arantxa goes behind her mother's back and reaches out to him with an urgent request. After receiving unexpected attention from a literary contest, Miren's son Gorka escapes Basque Country in pursuit of a different kind of life. Later, Miren discovers Arantxa's burgeoning friendship with Bittori.

summaries.short: Bittori, widow of a Basque businessman murdered by ETA, returns to her village to find out the truth about the crime.
summaries.full: Bittori, widow of a Basque businessman murdered by ETA, goes to the cemetery to speak with her deceased husband. The visit is a special one. A final ceasefire has been announced and she has decided to go back to the village where it all happened.

summaries.short: Series premiere. Following Basque separatist group ETA's ceasefire, Bittori demands answers for her late husband's unresolved murder.
summaries.full: Series premiere. When Basque separatist group ETA announces an end to more than forty years of violence, Bittori returns to her hometown in search of the full story behind her husband Txato's murder. But her arrival stokes neighborhood tensions and leaves Miren, Bittori's former best friend, particularly disturbed.

summaries.short: The hunt for Joxe Mari intensifies when he's placed on the Most Wanted Terrorist List. Bittori's children grow concerned about her health.
summaries.full: The hunt for Joxe Mari intensifies when he and fellow Oria command members are placed on the Most Wanted Terrorist list. After fulfilling her final promise to Txato, Nerea makes a monumental decision about her future. While Bittori meets with another member of Miren's family in secret, her children have a private meeting of their own.
